Benard Gitau @benagitau The government has integrated digital technologies in the Competence Based Curriculum (CBC), Education Cabinet secretary Amina Mohamed has said. She said this is aimed at cultivating and nurturing ICT skills right from primary school to put the country on a firm footing as far as ICT and innovation is concerned. “The government has focused on developing human capital. The Ministry of Education has undertaken to transform schools to become ‘the birthplaces of Kenya’s as Africa’s Silicon Savannah,” she said. She was speaking during the official commissioning of an ICT centre funded in collaboration with Korean government at Uhuru Gardens Primary School. Amina added that the government Digital Learning Programme (DLP) launched in 2013 targeting students in all public primary schools was making good progress.